Partly because those articles have been corrupted or paywalled by their hosters, I figured it‚Äôs time to republish the better part of my Cadborosaurus thoughts here at tetzoo.com. Plus I‚Äôve just produced some quantity of text on the subject for one my TetZoocryptomegathreads at Twitter. Ok‚Ä¶Cadborosaurus: the background. European colonists of coastal British Columbia, Canada and Washington, USA claimed ‚Äì from the 1880s onwards* ‚Äì to witness a large sea monster in the region‚Äôs coastal waters. Sometimes said to have a head shaped like that of a camel or horse, sometimes said to be hump-backed or serpentine, and sometimes said to be furry or hairy, or scaly, or wrinkled, it became associated in particular with British Columbia‚Äôs Cadboro Bay. In 1933, editor and journalist Archie H. Wills at the Victoria Daily Times adopted the name Cadborosaurus for this mystery sea creature, a moniker first suggested in a letter written to the Victoria Daily Times by I.
